def: A complete course or vibration; time of vibration, as of apendulum. [Obs.] Locke.
A pain about the heart. [Obs.] Chaucer.
Absolute. Diriment impediment (R. C. Ch.), an impediment thatnullifies marriage.
Attended by, or containing, an omen or omens; as, happy-omenedday.
Of or pertaining to the Ostracoidea.-- n.
One who makes or causes a nuisance.
Of or pertaining to recrement; consisting of recrement ordross. Boyle.

A book or table, containing a calendar of days, and months, towhich astronomical data and various statistics are often added, suchas the times of the rising and setting of the sun and moon, eclipses,hours of full tide, stated festivals of churches, terms of courts,etc. Nautical almanac, an almanac, or year book, containingastronomical calculations (lunar, stellar, etc.), and otherinformation useful to mariners.
To come or swing against something, or to shut, with suddenforce so as to produce a shock and noise; as, a door or shutterslams.
